    // Dispute Resolution Rules
    'fees.disputeResolutionRules.title': 'Dispute Resolution Rules',
    'fees.disputeResolutionRules.description': 'If you desire to resolve your dispute using Arbitalk\'s platform, you agree to be bound by its Dispute Resolution Rules ("Rules").\n\nThe Rules are designed to help you take maximum advantage of Arbitalk\'s online dispute resolution ("ODR") system and prevent needless litigation, safeguard yourself from adversities of disputes, and resolve them quickly, economically, effectively, and efficiently.\n\nSection 1 deals with preliminary aspects such as definitions, scope, modalities pertaining to communication, party obligations in respect of platform use, and data. Section 2 covers rules for arbitration proceedings on Arbitalk\'s ODR platform. Section 3 encapsulates rules for mediation/conciliation proceedings on Arbitalk\'s ODR platform.\n\nNote: If a dispute is referred for resolution to Arbitalk by a court, statutory authority, or governing body, then such disputes shall be resolved in accordance with the rules, regulations, and guidelines of the referring authority that are in effect as of the date on which the request is made to Arbitalk.',
    'fees.disputeResolutionRules.scope.title': 'Scope and Application',
    'fees.disputeResolutionRules.scope.description': 'These rules apply to all disputes submitted to Arbitalk for resolution through arbitration, mediation, or conciliation. The rules are designed to be consistent with the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, and other applicable Indian laws.',
    'fees.disputeResolutionRules.procedures.title': 'Procedures and Timelines',
    'fees.disputeResolutionRules.procedures.description': 'All proceedings follow structured timelines: Mediation (30-60 days), Conciliation (45-75 days), and Arbitration (60-90 days). Parties are required to submit all relevant documents and information within specified deadlines.',
    'fees.disputeResolutionRules.confidentiality.title': 'Confidentiality',
    'fees.disputeResolutionRules.confidentiality.description': 'All proceedings conducted through Arbitalk are strictly confidential. Information disclosed during the process cannot be used in any other forum without the express consent of all parties involved.',
    'fees.disputeResolutionRules.enforcement.title': 'Enforcement of Awards',
    'fees.disputeResolutionRules.enforcement.description': 'Arbitral awards issued through Arbitalk are binding and enforceable under the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996. Mediation and conciliation settlements are enforceable as contracts between the parties.',
    
    // Code of Conduct and Disclosure Rules
    'fees.codeOfConduct.title': 'Arbitrators\' and Mediators\' Code of Conduct and Disclosure Rules',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.description': 'The Arbitrators\' and Mediators\' Code of Conduct and Disclosure Rules ("Code") set out the general framework for ethics with which the arbitrators and mediators/conciliators empanelled with Arbitalk shall conduct the arbitration and mediation/conciliation proceedings, respectively.\n\nThe Code also governs the disclosure requirements to act as an arbitrator or a mediator/conciliator.\n\nWhile Section 1 deals with preliminary aspects such as definitions, scope, modalities pertaining to communication, and arbitrators\' and mediators\'/conciliators\' obligations in respect of platform use, Section 2 and 3 govern the code of conduct and disclosure rules for arbitrators and mediators/conciliators empanelled with Arbitalk, respectively.\n\n',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.clickHere': 'Click here',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.clickHereSuffix': 'to access the governing documents for resolving disputes on Arbitalk\'s ODR platform.',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.independence.title': 'Independence and Impartiality',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.independence.description': 'Arbitrators and mediators must be independent and impartial. They must not have any financial, personal, or professional relationship with any party that could affect their judgment or create an appearance of bias.',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.disclosure.title': 'Disclosure Requirements',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.disclosure.description': 'Before accepting an appointment, arbitrators and mediators must disclose any circumstances that might give rise to justifiable doubts about their independence or impartiality. This includes any past or present relationships with the parties, their representatives, or the subject matter of the dispute.',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.impartiality.title': 'Duty of Impartiality',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.impartiality.description': 'Throughout the proceedings, arbitrators and mediators must remain impartial and treat all parties equally. They must not favor any party and must base their decisions solely on the facts and applicable law.',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.competence.title': 'Competence and Diligence',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.competence.description': 'Arbitrators and mediators must possess the necessary qualifications, experience, and expertise to handle the dispute competently. They must conduct proceedings diligently and efficiently, ensuring timely resolution.',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.confidentiality.title': 'Confidentiality Obligations',
    'fees.codeOfConduct.confidentiality.description': 'Arbitrators and mediators must maintain strict confidentiality regarding all information disclosed during the proceedings. They must not disclose any confidential information to third parties without the express consent of all parties involved.',
    
